Title:

Efficiency in Order: Visualization of Sorting Algorithms

1. Introduction

Sorting is one of the most fundamental operations in computer science, used to arrange data in a specific order for easier processing and searching.
This project, Sorting Visualizer, aims to demonstrate the working of various sorting algorithms through a visual representation. It helps users understand how each algorithm sorts an array step by step.

2. Objectives

To visualize and compare different sorting algorithms.

To provide a clear understanding of algorithm behavior through animations.

To build an interactive and educational web-based tool.

