4. Algorithms Implemented

Bubble Sort ‚Äì Compares adjacent elements and swaps if needed.

Insertion Sort ‚Äì Builds the sorted array one element at a time.

Selection Sort ‚Äì Finds the minimum element and places it in sorted order.

Merge Sort ‚Äì Uses divide and conquer technique to split and merge arrays.

Quick Sort ‚Äì Uses partitioning and recursion for efficient sorting.

5. Working Principle

The program generates an array of random bars representing unsorted numbers.

When the user selects a sorting algorithm and clicks the ‚ÄúStart‚Äù button, the corresponding algorithm runs.

Each comparison or swap is visually represented through color changes and movement.

The animation continues until the array becomes fully sorted.

